# 6. Deployment and Operations

## 6.1 Deployment Architecture

### 6.1.1 Kubernetes Deployment

**Cluster Configuration:**
- Kubernetes 1.28+
- 3 availability zones per region
- Minimum 6 worker nodes per cluster
- Automatic node scaling enabled

**Deployment Pipeline:**

<<mermaid>>
  graph LR
    A[Code Push] --> B[GitHub Actions]
    B --> C{Tests Pass?}
    C -->|Yes| D[Build Docker Image]
    C -->|No| E[Notify Developers]
    D --> F[Push to Registry]
    F --> G[Deploy to Staging]
    G --> H{Smoke Tests Pass?}
    H -->|Yes| I[Deploy to Production]
    H -->|No| E
    I --> J[Health Checks]
    J --> K{Healthy?}
    K -->|Yes| L[Complete]
    K -->|No| M[Rollback]
    
    style C fill:#FBBC04,color:#000
    style H fill:#FBBC04,color:#000
    style K fill:#FBBC04,color:#000
    style I fill:#34A853,color:#fff
    style M fill:#EA4335,color:#fff

*Figure 4: Continuous deployment pipeline with automated rollback*

## 6.2 Monitoring and Observability

### 6.2.1 Metrics

**Key Metrics Tracked:**
- Request rate (requests per second)
- Error rate (errors per second)
- Latency (p50, p95, p99)
- Saturation (CPU, memory, disk)

**Monitoring Stack:**
- Prometheus for metrics collection
- Grafana for visualization
- AlertManager for alerting
- PagerDuty for on-call rotation

### 6.2.2 Logging

**Structured Logging Format:**

```json
{
  "timestamp": "2024-10-08T10:30:45Z",
  "level": "INFO",
  "service": "user-service",
  "trace_id": "7f8b9d0e1c2a3b4c",
  "user_id": "usr_123",
  "method": "GET",
  "path": "/v3/users/usr_123",
  "status": 200,
  "latency_ms": 42,
  "message": "User retrieved successfully"
}
```

**Log Aggregation:**
- ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana)
- 30-day retention for operational logs
- 1-year retention for audit logs

