# 7. Appendix

## 7.1 Glossary

**API (Application Programming Interface)**
: A set of protocols and tools for building software applications

**JWT (JSON Web Token)**
: A compact, URL-safe token format for representing claims between two parties

**Microservices**
: Architectural style where applications are structured as collections of loosely coupled services

**OAuth 2.0**
: Industry-standard protocol for authorization

**REST (Representational State Transfer)**
: Architectural style for distributed hypermedia systems

**RBAC (Role-Based Access Control)**
: Method of regulating access based on user roles

